<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center; text-align:center;">
<hr />
<b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Afghanistan" title="Portal:Afghanistan">Afghanistan Portal</a></b><br />
&#160;<span class="noprint plainlinksneverexpand" style="white-space: nowrap; font-size:xx-small;"><a href="/wiki/Template:History_of_Afghanistan" title="Template:History of Afghanistan">v</a>&#160;•&#160;<a href="/wiki/Template_talk:History_of_Afghanistan" title="Template talk:History of Afghanistan"><span title="Discussion about this template.">d</span></a>&#160;•&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:History_of_Afghanistan&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:History_of_Afghanistan&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow"><span style="color:#002bb8;" title="You can edit this template. Please use the preview button before saving.">e</span></a></span>&#160;</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>The <b>Soviet war in <a href="/wiki/Afghanistan" title="Afghanistan">Afghanistan</a></b> (also known as the <b>Soviet-Afghan War</b> or the <b>Soviet Invasion of Afghanistan</b>) was a nine-year <a href="/wiki/War" title="War">conflict</a> involving <a href="/wiki/Soviet_Union" title="Soviet Union">Soviet Union</a> <a href="/wiki/Military_of_the_Soviet_Union" title="Military of the Soviet Union" class="mw-redirect">forces</a> supporting the <a href="/wiki/Marxism" title="Marxism">Marxist</a> <a href="/wiki/People%27s_Democratic_Party_of_Afghanistan" title="People's Democratic Party of Afghanistan">People's Democratic Party of Afghanistan</a> (PDPA) <a href="/wiki/Government" title="Government">government</a> against the <a href="/wiki/Mujahideen#Afghanistan" title="Mujahideen">mujahideen</a> <a href="/wiki/Resistance_movement" title="Resistance movement">resistance</a>. The latter group found support from a variety of sources including the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a>, <a href="/wiki/Saudi_Arabia" title="Saudi Arabia">Saudi Arabia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Pakistan" title="Pakistan">Pakistan</a> and other <a href="/wiki/Muslim" title="Muslim">Muslim</a> nations in <a href="/wiki/Proxy_war#Cold_War" title="Proxy war">the context of</a> the <a href="/wiki/Cold_War" title="Cold War">Cold War</a>. This conflict was concurrent to the <a href="/wiki/1979_Iranian_Revolution" title="1979 Iranian Revolution" class="mw-redirect">1979 Iranian Revolution</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93Iraq_War" title="Iran–Iraq War">Iran–Iraq War</a>.</p>
<p>The initial <a href="#1979:_Soviet_deployment" title="">Soviet deployment</a> of the <a href="/wiki/40th_Army_(Soviet_Union)" title="40th Army (Soviet Union)">40th Army</a> in Afghanistan began on December 24, 1979.<sup id="cite_ref-bbc_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bbc-5" title=""><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup> The final <a href="#Phase_four:_withdrawal_.28January_1987_to_February_1989.29" title="">troop withdrawal</a> began on May 15, 1988, and ended on February 15, 1989. Due to the interminable nature of the war, the conflict in Afghanistan has often been referred to as the Soviet equivalent of the United States' <a href="/wiki/Vietnam_War" title="Vietnam War">Vietnam War</a>.</p>
